le=\"font-size: 9pt\">List of accolades received by ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''</span>\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[File:Robert Downey, Jr. 2012.jpg|center|200px|alt=Robert Downey Jr. at the Avengers Assemble premiere at Westfield Shopping Centre in Shepherd's Bush, London 2012.]] [[Robert Downey Jr.]] received the most acting nominations for ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' with a total of ten.\n|-\n| colspan=3 |\n{| class=\"collapsible collapsed\" width=100%\n! colspan=3 style=\"background-color: #D9E8FF; text-align: center;\" | Accolades\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff; text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Award'''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#cec; text-size:0.9em; width:50px;\"| '''Won'''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#fcd; text-size:0.9em; width:50px;\"| '''Nominated'''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Academy Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Annie Awards]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|2}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Bradbury Award]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[British Academy Film Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Critics' Choice Movie Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|3}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Detroit Film Critics Society]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Empire Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|5}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Motion Picture Sound Editors|Golden Reel Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Golden Trailer Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|2}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Hollywood Film Festival]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Hugo Award]]s\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[MTV Movie Awards]]\n|{{won|3}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[People's Choice Awards]]\n|{{won|3}}\n|{{nom|13}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Saturn Awards]]\n|{{won|4}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association]]\n|{{won|0}}\n|{{nom|1}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Taurus World Stunt Awards]]\n|{{won|4}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|{{won|2}}\n|{{nom|11}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n;[[Visual Effects Society]]\n|{{won|2}}\n|{{nom|6}}\n|}\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"|\n;Total number of awards and nominations\n|-\n|{{won|'''Totals'''}}\n|{{won|'''21'''}}\n|{{nom|'''74'''}}\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff;\"\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"font-size: smaller; text-align:center;\" | [[#References|References]]\n|}\n''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|Marvel's The Avengers]]'' (''Marvel Avengers Assemble'' in the UK and Ireland), more commonly known as ''The Avengers'', is a 2012 American [[superhero film]], scripted and directed by [[Joss Whedon]], based on the [[Marvel Comics]] superhero team [[Avengers (comics)|of the same name]]. The film stars an ensemble cast consisting of [[Robert Downey Jr.]], [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], [[Mark Ruffalo]], [[Chris Hemsworth]], [[Scarlett Johansson]], [[Jeremy Renner]], [[Tom Hiddleston]], [[Clark Gregg]], [[Cobie Smulders]], [[Stellan Skarsg\u00e5rd]] and [[Samuel L. Jackson]]. In ''The Avengers'', [[Nick Fury]] (Jackson), director of the peacekeeping organization [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], recruits [[Tony Stark (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Iron Man]] (Downey), [[Steve Rogers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Captain America]] (Evans), the [[Bruce Banner (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Hulk]] (Ruffalo), and [[Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Thor]] (Hemsworth) to form a team that must stop Thor's adoptive brother [[Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Loki]] (Hiddleston) from subjugating Earth.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/447928/The-Avengers/cast|title=The Avengers (2012) - Acting Credits|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=September 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ebert|first=Roger|url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-avengers-2012|title=The Avengers Movie Review & Film Summary|publisher=Roger Ebert|date=May 2, 2012|accessdate=September 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n''The Avengers'', produced on a budget of $220 million, was released theatrically in the United States on May 4, 2012 and grossed a worldwide total of over $1.5 billion.<ref name=\"BOM\" /> The film has garnered numerous awards and nominations with most nominations recognizing the film itself, the performances of the cast (particularly those of Downey, Johansson and Hemsworth) and the film's visual effects. ''The Avengers'' was nominated for an [[Academy Award for Best Visual Effects]] and a [[BAFTA Award for Best Special Visual Effects]]. The film was also nominated for three [[Critics' Choice Movie Awards]], five [[Empire Awards]], six [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]], six [[MTV Movie Awards]] (winning three), thirteen [[People's Choice Awards]] (winning three), six [[Saturn Awards]] (winning four), eleven [[Teen Choice Awards]] (winning two), and six [[Visual Effects Society|VES Awards]] (winning two).\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Ceremony{{efn|Each date is linked to the article about the awards held that year, wherever possible.}}\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Golden Trailer Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| May 31, 2012\n| Summer 2012 Blockbuster Trailer\n| {{sort|Avengers, The|''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' \"Personal\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"goldentrailer\" />\n|-\n| Best Action TV Spot\n| {{sort|Avengers, The|''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' \"Become\"}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[2012 Teen Choice Awards|July 22, 2012]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie - Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| {{sort|Avengers, The|''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''}}\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"AccoTeenChoice\"/><br /><ref name=\"AccoTeenChoice2\"/><br /><ref name=\"AccoTeenChoice3\"/>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actor - Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actor: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| {{sort|Hemsworth|[[Chris Hemsworth]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| {{sort|Downey|[[Robert Downey Jr.]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Actress: Sci-Fi/Fantasy\n| {{sort|Johansson|[[Scarlett Johansson]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Hissy Fit|Choice Movie: Hissy Fit]]\n| {{sort|Ruffalo|[[Mark Ruffalo]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain|Choice Movie: Villain]]\n| {{sort|Hiddleston|[[Tom Hiddleston]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie: Male Scene Stealer\n| {{sort|Evans|[[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Summer Movie: Action\n| {{sort|Avengers, The|''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Choice Summer Movie Star: Male\n| {{sort|Downey|[[Robert Downey Jr.]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| {{sort|Hemsworth|[[Chris Hemsworth]]}} {{small|(''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' and ''[[Snow White and the Huntsman]]'')}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Choice Summer Movie Star: Female\n| {{sort|Johansson|[[Scarlett Johansson]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:cente