9glise Trophy]] (representing the Continent of Europe): 1994, 1995, 1996 (winners), 1997, 1998\n*[[Junior Ryder Cup]] (representing Europe): 1995 (winners), 1997\n*[[Eisenhower Trophy]] (representing Spain): [[1996 Eisenhower Trophy|1996]], [[1998 Eisenhower Trophy|1998]]\n*[[St Andrews Trophy]] (representing the Continent of Europe): 1996\n\n'''Professional'''\n*[[Alfred Dunhill Cup]] (representing Spain): [[1999 Alfred Dunhill Cup|1999]] (winners)\n*[[Ryder Cup]] (representing Europe): [[1999 Ryder Cup|1999]], [[2002 Ryder Cup|2002]] (winners), [[2004 Ryder Cup|2004]] (winners), [[2006 Ryder Cup|2006]] (winners), [[2008 Ryder Cup|2008]], [[2012 Ryder Cup|2012]] (winners), [[2014 Ryder Cup|2014]] (winners), [[2016 Ryder Cup|2016]], [[2018 Ryder Cup|2018]] (winners)\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Ryder Cup points record\n! 1999!! 2002!! 2004!! 2006!! 2008!! 2012!! 2014!! 2016!! 2018!! Total \n|-\n|3.5||3||4.5||4||1||2||2.5||2||3|| 25.5\n|}\n\n*[[Seve Trophy]] (representing Continental Europe): [[2000 Seve Trophy|2000]] (winners), [[2003 Seve Trophy|2003]]\n*[[World Cup (men's golf)|World Cup]] (representing Spain): [[2001 WGC-World Cup|2001]], [[2004 WGC-World Cup|2004]], [[2005 WGC-World Cup|2005]], [[2009 Omega Mission Hills World Cup|2009]]\n\n==Golf equipment==\n[[Image:Sergio Garcia-La Temp\u00eate 02.jpg|thumb|200px|Garc\u00eda at the 2009 [[Telus Skins Game|Telus World Skins Game]] in [[L\u00e9vis]], Canada]]\nGarc\u00eda previously had an endorsement deal with [[TaylorMade]] and [[Adidas]], at the time a joint company<ref name=\"sponsorship\">{{cite web |title=TaylorMade PGA Tour Players: Sergio Garc\u00eda |publisher=TaylorMade Golf |url=http://www.taylormadegolf.com/players.asp?tID=2&pID=152 |accessdate=15 April 2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061119022119/http://www.taylormadegolf.com/players.asp?tID=2&pID=152 |archivedate=19 November 2006}}</ref> used all TaylorMade equipment, and Adidas shoes and clothing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pga.com/golf-equipment/winners-bag/whats-in-winners-bags-week-december-15-2013 |title=What's in the winners' bags for the week of December 15, 2013 |publisher=PGA of America |accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the acquisition of TaylorMade by [[KPS Capital Partners]] and separation from Adidas and after fifteen years with the company, in January 2018 Sergio Garc\u00eda severed his ties with TaylorMade, remained with Adidas and signed with [[Callaway Golf Company|Callaway]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Heath |first=Elliot|title=Sergio Garcia What\u2019s In The Bag? |url=http://www.golf-monthly.co.uk/gear/gear-news/sergio-garcia-whats-in-the-bag-2-149595#rLdgZ2pHdqrD92bR.99 |magazine=Golf Monthly |date=24 January 2018 |access-date=4 May 2018}}</ref> At the start of 2020, Garcia confirmed he had parted ways with Callaway after two years to become a free agent.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of golfers with most European Tour wins]]\n*[[List of golfers with most PGA Tour wins]]\n*[[List of golfers with most Asian Tour wins]]\n*[[Monday Night Golf]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Sergio Garcia}}\n*{{official website|http://www.sergiogarcia.com}}\n*{{EuroTour player|487}}\n*{{PGATour player|21209}}\n*{{OWGR|5689}}\n*[http://sport.guardian.co.uk/golf/story/0,,1890176,00.html Interview] \u2013 ''[[The Observer]]'', 8 October 2006\n\n{{The Masters champions}}\n{{Sir Henry Cotton Rookies of the Year}}\n{{European Tour Golfer of the Year}}\n{{navboxes|title=Sergio Garc\u00eda in the [[Ryder Cup]]\n|list1={{1999 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2002 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2004 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2006 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2008 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2012 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2014 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2016 European Ryder Cup team}}\n{{2018 European Ryder Cup team}}\n}}\n{{Laureus World Breakthough of the Year}}\n{{Players Championship champions}}\n\n{{Authority co